To say a viewer of Reina’s archives didn’t “learn anything” or gain insight is a purposeful dismissal of Reina’s work and contributions.
I learned about enduring sisterhood as Sylvia mourned Marsha’s while she lived in a shack on the Christopher Street piers.
I saw Sylvia’s “y’all better quiet down” speech from 1973 which still affirms me and teaches me today. I show it during every speech I give.
I heard Marsha’s & Sylvia’s voices for the first time from her archives. Reina proved our heroines were HERE after years of erasure.
